President Barack Obama has proclaimed March 31, 2015, as Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of education and the potential of every child to change the world. He honors Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, the Lubavitcher Rebbe, for his dedication to promoting education as the cornerstone of humanity. The Rebbe worked to break down barriers for girls who wanted to learn, and his legacy calls for continued efforts to provide quality education for all. President Obama also highlights the Let Girls Learn initiative, aimed at increasing the number of girls in school worldwide. He reaffirms his commitment to improving education in the United States, including expanding access to preschool and higher education. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe Education and Sharing Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.